news.title: After HC order, panchayats in Goa to act against illegal constructions
news.para: In its detailed March 6 order, the high court issued several directions to authorities as they go about removing illegal constructions and put measures in place.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government creates 125 new towns in eight years
news.para: Principal secretary of the department, Amrit Abhijat said that presently 21 schemes to strengthen urban services, infrastructure and social sectors are being run.

news.title: BDA approves building plans for 158 high-rises in Bhubaneswar despite BMC's authority
news.para: Responding to a query by legislator Upasana Mohapatra, the minister stated that as per information received from BDA, it accorded building plan approvals to 158 high-rises and received sanction fees of Rs 48.30 crore in the past five years.

news.title: Indore: IDA may propose Rs 1,650 crore budget for  new residential schemes
news.para: There is also a plan to initiate the construction of a convention centre with a capacity of around 10,000 on approximately 17 hectares of land near the Super Corridor. Besides, the IDA is contemplating developing two new ISBTs on Bhopal and Dhar Road.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 1,850 properties of tax defaulters
news.para: The civic body issued 3,928 notices to residential property owners who had not cleared their property tax dues. AMC officials cautioned that failure to pay would result in disconnection of water and sewerage services.

news.title: BirlaNu plans to invest $150 million by 2028
news.para: "We’ve doubled our AAC block capacity in Chennai to four lakh cubic meters per year and are marking our expansion into the home and interiors space, said Akshat Seth, managing director and CEO of BirlaNu.

news.title: Atmosphere Realty achieves early NCD redemption of Rs 217.9 crore
news.para: ARPL had issued 2,179 debentures at a face value of Rs 10 lakh each aggregating to Rs 217.9 crore on December 9, 2020. These NCDs were acquired by Marubeni Corporation, a Japanese conglomerate.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires 6.54 acre land from CIDCO in Navi Mumbai for Rs 717 crore
news.para: The total land area is 26,478 sq meters (6.54 acre), with a total value of Rs. 716.58 crore. All the agreements have a total tenure of 60 years.

news.title: Odisha government eases fire safety certification for pre-2017 buildings
news.para: "The provision exclusively applies to buildings constructed before 2017, which marks the year when Odisha Fire Prevention and Fire Safety Rules, 2017 came into effect," director general (fire and emergency services), Sudhanshu Sarangi, told TOI.

news.title: Chandigarh urban planning department approves Manimajra housing project layout
news.para: The MC aims to earn Rs 250 to 300 crore by auctioning this prime land. The civic body authority will now proceed to finalise the terms and conditions, and related aspects to maximise revenue from the land disposal.

news.title: Sebi puts WeWork India's IPO on abeyance
news.para: As per the DRHP, Embassy Buildcon offered to sell up to 3.3 crore shares, while Ariel Way Tenant, through which WeWork Inc holds stake in the Indian company, is seeking to offer about 1 crore shares.

news.title: Years gone, plot handover held up, Ramprastha City buyers turn to Haryana CM
news.para: Many, now senior citizens, fear the land may be sold to other developers. The buyers' association, led by Sanjay Jain and Sanjay Arora, accused the company of deliberate delays and misleading assurances.

news.title: Bengaluru: Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout allottees demand faster infrastructure work
news.para: The K-RERA resumed hearing on the Nadaprabhu Kempe­gowda Layout on Monday after a gap of two-and-a-half years. The last hearing of the petition filed by site allottees was held in 2022.

news.title: Bombay HC upholds CIDCO's stop work notice for Ulwe project amid land title dispute
news.para: The HC held that the Navi Mumbai planning agency, City and Industrial Development Corporation (CIDCO), was right in stopping construction work undertaken by Bhosale Homes, as land ownership was under dispute.

news.title: Mumbai: Over 63,000 tenements in Dharavi surveyed
news.para: With more than 63,000 tenements already surveyed - and counting - the present survey has gone well beyond the earlier benchmark of approximately 60,000 ground-floor tenements, officials said.

news.title: DLF buys 49.99% stake in DLF Urban from GIC arm for Rs 497 crore
news.para: With this deal, DLF will have a 100 per cent stake in DLF Urban, which has developed a luxury housing project in the national capital.

news.title: Holcim's spin-off Amrize targets robust growth through 2028 in USA
news.para: An Amrize listing by the end of the first half of 2025 remains on track, the company said in a statement ahead of its investor day in New York. Holcim targeted a $30 billion valuation when the spin-off was first announced in January 2024.

news.title: UK's warehouse REIT evaluates Blackstone's $633 million takeover proposal
news.para: The 115 pence-per-share proposal is a 4% increase from the previous one made jointly by Blackstone and global investment firm Sixth Street Partners.

news.title: UK: Bellway's profit rises 12% amid lower mortgage rates
news.para: Home sales in the UK got a boost in the first quarter as homebuyers tried to complete purchases before a property tax exemption expires from April 1 and by more UK rate cuts, although the pace of rate cuts is slow.

news.title: Citigroup leases 7.7 lakh sq ft office space in Pune's Kharadi for Rs 1,100 crore
news.para: The entire space is spread over 7th to 16th floor of Panchshil Business Hub and starting monthly rentals range between nearly Rs 2.02 crore to Rs 2.71 crore depending on the floor.
